{{define "main"}}
<section class='hero hero--compact'>
    <div>
        <p class='eyebrow'>About the notebook</p>
        <h2>Snippetbox is a compact archive for code and context.</h2>
        <p class='lede'>Built in Go, it focuses on the less glamorous but durable parts of web work: routing, templates, sessions, auth, validation, persistence, caching, and transport security.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class='panel prose'>
    <p>Snippetbox is a small web application written in Go by <a href='https://github.com/aartchik'>aartchik</a> that lets users create, store, and manage text snippets.</p>
    <p>The project is also a practical exercise in building secure server-rendered applications with real backend patterns instead of toy examples.</p>

    <h3>Stack</h3>
    <ul class='tag-list'>
        <li><strong>Go</strong> with `net/http`</li>
        <li><strong>html/template</strong> for server rendering</li>
        <li><strong>MySQL</strong> for users, snippets, and sessions</li>
        <li><strong>scs</strong> for session management</li>
        <li><strong>nosurf</strong> for CSRF protection</li>
        <li><strong>httprouter</strong> for request routing</li>
        <li><strong>alice</strong> for middleware composition</li>
        <li><strong>Redis</strong> for cache reads</li>
    </ul>
</section>
{{end}}


